# Admin User Management — Implementation Plan

## Goal

Add a `/admin/users` section to the admin panel that gives authorized staff full
visibility into every registered user and the ability to promote plans and adjust
attempt quotas without touching the database directly.

---

## What Will Be Built

### Admin can see (read)
| Column | Source |
|---|---|
| Full name + email | `users` table |
| Plan (starter / pro / ultra) | `users.plan` |
| Member since | `users.created_at` |
| Last active | `users.last_active_date` |
| Speaking attempts used (total) | `COUNT(attempts)` where skill=speaking |
| Writing attempts used (total) | `COUNT(attempts)` where skill=writing |
| Attempts remaining (per plan limits) | computed from plan limits |
| Role (user / admin) | `users.is_admin` |
| Streak | `users.streak_days` |

### Admin can do (write)
| Action | Effect |
|---|---|
| **Change plan** | Updates `users.plan`, writes audit log |
| **Grant bonus attempts** | Inserts rows into a new `attempt_overrides` table OR updates a bonus column on `users`. Plan below. |
| **Toggle admin role** | Flips `users.is_admin` |
| **Reset streak** | Sets `users.streak_days = 0` |

---

## Design Decisions

### Bonus attempt approach — `attempt_overrides` table (recommended)

Instead of storing `bonus_speaking_attempts INT` on `users` (which bloats the
users table and obscures intent), introduce a dedicated table:

```sql
CREATE TABLE attempt_overrides (
    id            UUID PRIMARY KEY DEFAULT gen_random_uuid(),
    user_id       UUID NOT NULL REFERENCES users(id) ON DELETE CASCADE,
    skill         TEXT NOT NULL CHECK (skill IN ('speaking', 'writing')),
    bonus_count   INT  NOT NULL DEFAULT 0,
    granted_by    UUID REFERENCES users(id),
    note          TEXT,
    created_at    TIMESTAMPTZ NOT NULL DEFAULT NOW(),
    UNIQUE(user_id, skill)   -- one override row per user per skill
);
```

The quota engine (`app/core/quota.py`) already computes `per_task` limits from the
plan. It will read the bonus and add it on top:

```
effective_limit = plan_limit + bonus_count
```

This keeps the quota logic clean, auditable, and reversible.

> [!IMPORTANT]
> This requires a new Alembic migration. No existing tables are modified.

