## Proposed Changes

### Backend

---

#### [NEW] `app/models/attempt_override.py`

New SQLAlchemy model for `attempt_overrides` table.

#### [NEW] `alembic/versions/xxx_add_attempt_overrides.py`

Migration that creates the `attempt_overrides` table.

#### [NEW] `app/repositories/admin_user_repo.py`

```python
class AdminUserRepository:
    async def list_users(search, plan_filter, page, per_page) -> list[User]
    async def count_users(search, plan_filter) -> int
    async def get_user_with_stats(user_id) -> UserWithStats
    async def update_plan(user, new_plan) -> User
    async def toggle_admin(user) -> User
    async def set_bonus_attempts(user_id, skill, bonus_count, granted_by) -> AttemptOverride
    async def reset_streak(user) -> User
```

All queries are single efficient SQL calls — no N+1.

#### [NEW] `app/api/v1/admin_users.py`

New FastAPI router, all behind `require_admin`:

```
GET  /admin/users                     — paginated user list with stats
GET  /admin/users/{user_id}           — single user detail + full quota
PATCH /admin/users/{user_id}/plan     — change plan { plan: "pro" }
PATCH /admin/users/{user_id}/attempts — set bonus attempts { skill, bonus_count, note }
PATCH /admin/users/{user_id}/role     — toggle is_admin { is_admin: bool }
PATCH /admin/users/{user_id}/streak   — reset streak { streak_days: 0 }
```

Every PATCH writes an `admin_audit_logs` entry (entity_type="user", action_type="update").

#### [MODIFY] `app/api/router.py`

Register the new `admin_users` router:
```python
api_router.include_router(admin_users.router, prefix="/admin", tags=["Admin — Users"])
```

#### [MODIFY] `app/core/quota.py`

Update `get_plan_limits()` to accept and add `bonus_count` from `attempt_overrides`
when computing `effective_limit`.

